name: Sin City X iamYork
description:
This is a model trained on the art style of Frank Miller who is famous for his Sin City, 300 and Batman graphic novels among others... The model is trained on the comics, not the film adaptations...

Sin City: Add this to the end of your text prompts: sinCity_iamYork

Suggested Settings:

Steps: 40-100, CFG Scale: 7-12

Add this prompt for additional look: "black and red color scheme"

There are two versions: v2000 is more solid and the iamYork version is a bit more gritty...

I would love to see what you create with this model... and if you need additional info on using the models and/or just additional Stable Diffusion and AI knowledge come "JOIN US" at my YT channel

"Common Sense Made Simple" https://www.youtube.com/c/CommonSenseMadeSimple

Here is an example using the model for animation: https://youtu.be/Fan4ylOaioc

Custom Model trained by N.F. Tengri of https://iamyork.com/

iamYork is a boutique Anti-Design, Animation, and Visual Effects studio in Hell's kitchen, New York City...

Here is Frank Miller's website if you would like to learn more about him and his amazing work: https://frankmillerink.com/

DISCLAIMER: This model is trained on the art stylings of Frank Miller... Using it for commercial use is at your own risk... Any models I train based on artist styles I only use for personal and/or experimentation purposes...
